  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n*Summary*: user picture is shown for each message when user send to public chat several messages in a row\r\n* NOTE:  issue can be replicated only on current chat, so if you open channel with unread messages - only one user picture is displayed (as expected) \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\none picture is displayed for all messages\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nleft side - expected (like in mobile client);\r\nright side - current behavior on desktop\r\n![publ_chat](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42620614-195227c0-85c4-11e8-806a-1ebd0d14dd84.png)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n* Prerequisites: \r\nUser A: uses status-desktop\r\nUser B: uses status-mobile\r\n\r\n1) (User A) Open Status\r\n2) (User A) Click on +\r\n3) (User A) Join to any public chat (i.e. `#test`)\r\n4) (User B) Join the same public chat; send several messages in a row; User A should have the public channel opened when User B sends messages.\r\n5) (User A) check public chat \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: [desktop_build_11.07.2018](https://jenkins.status.im/job/status-react/job/desktop/job/manual/47/)\r\n* Operating System: Mac OSx High Sierra\r\n",
